## Recommended Tech Stack

### Core Framework
| Choice | Version | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **Next.js 15** | App Router | SSR for SEO, server components reduce bundle size, built-in routing, API Routes as BFF layer if needed |
| **TypeScript** | 5.x | Type safety, matches backend TypeScript conventions |
| **React** | 19 | Latest with concurrent features |

### UI & Styling
| Choice | Why |
|---|---|
| **Tailwind CSS v4** | Utility-first, perfect for rapid iteration, great dark mode support |
| **shadcn/ui** | Production-grade headless components (built on Radix UI), dark mode native, fully customizable |
| **Framer Motion** | Premium animations вЂ” page transitions, card reveals, number counters |
| **Lucide React** | Icon library that pairs perfectly with shadcn |

### Data & State
| Choice | Why |
|---|---|
| **TanStack Query v5** | Server state management, background refetch, optimistic updates, cache invalidation |
| **Zustand** | Lightweight auth state (`{ user, token, setUser, logout }`), UI state flags, WebSocket subscription state |
| **Axios** | Consistent HTTP client with interceptors (auto-attach JWT, handle 401) |

### Real-Time
| Choice | Why |
|---|---|
| **Socket.io Client** | Matches backend Socket.io server exactly; auto-reconnect, room subscriptions |

### Charts & Data Visualization
| Choice | Why |
|---|---|
| **Recharts** | React-native, composable, works with SSR |
| **Tremor** (optional) | Ready-made dashboard chart components built on Recharts |

### Forms & Validation
| Choice | Why |
|---|---|
| **React Hook Form** | Performance, minimal re-renders |
| **Zod** | Schema validation matching backend validation patterns |

### Developer Experience
| Choice | Why |
|---|---|
| **ESLint + Prettier** | Code quality |
| **next-themes** | Light/dark mode toggle with zero flash |

