## Page-by-Page Specification

### Page 1: Login / Register (`/login`, `/register`)
**Goal**: Beautiful auth screen with brand identity.

**Components**:
- Animated logo + tagline ("AI-Powered Observability with a Prompt Firewall")
- Email / Password form with Zod validation
- Toggle between Login and Register
- Error state handling

**API calls**:
- `POST /users/login` в†’ store JWT + user in Zustand + localStorage
- `POST /users/register`

**Design**: Full-screen dark background with a glowing indigo radial gradient. Card with glassmorphism effect.

---

### Page 2: Dashboard Overview (`/`)
**Goal**: Command center вЂ” answer "What's happening right now?"

**Sections**:
1. **Stats Row** вЂ” 5 animated count-up cards:
   - Total Incidents (with delta vs yesterday)
   - Open Incidents (orange glow when > 0)
   - Critical Incidents (red pulsing dot when > 0)
   - Unacknowledged Alerts (red badge)
   - Avg AI Confidence (% with progress bar)

2. **Charts Row**:
   - `TrendChart` вЂ” 7-day area chart of incident volume
   - `SeverityChart` вЂ” Donut with critical/high/medium/low breakdown

3. **Recent Incidents** вЂ” Live-updating table with last 10 incidents  
   - Real-time: new rows slide in when `incident:created` WS event fires

4. **Active Alerts Banner** вЂ” sticky bar at top when unacknowledged alerts exist

**API calls**: `GET /stats`, `GET /incidents?limit=10`, `GET /alerts?acknowledged=false`
**Real-time**: Subscribe `incidents` + `alerts` rooms

---

### Page 3: Incidents List (`/incidents`)
**Goal**: Full operational incident management table.

**Components**:
- `IncidentFilters`: status multi-select, severity multi-select, date range picker, search input
- `IncidentTable`: columns: ID, title, source, severity badge, status badge, AI confidence bar, created_at, actions
- Pagination controls
- **View toggle**: Table в†” Card grid
- **Create Incident** button в†’ modal with form

**Real-time**: When `incident:created` fires в†’ toast notification + row appears at top with animation

**API calls**: `GET /incidents` with query params, `POST /incidents`, `DELETE /incidents/:id`

---

### Page 4: Incident Detail (`/incidents/:id`)
**Goal**: Deep-dive view вЂ” the "money page" of the product.

**Layout**: Two-column (2/3 left, 1/3 right)

**Left Column**:
1. **Header**: Title, severity badge, status badge w/ inline dropdown to change status, source, created_at
2. **AI Analysis Card** (`AIAnalysisCard`):
   - Summary (paragraph text)
   - Root Cause (highlighted block)
   - Resolution (action items list)
   - Confidence score with color-coded bar (green >0.8, yellow >0.6, red <0.5)
   - "Analysis powered by Gemini 2.5 Flash" footer badge
3. **Sanitized Log Viewer** (`SanitizedLogViewer`):
   - Monospace code block with syntax-like highlighting
   - `[REDACTED_EMAIL]`, `[REDACTED_IP]`, etc. highlighted in amber/red badges
4. **Audit Timeline** (`AuditTimeline`):
   - Vertical timeline of all audit_logs for this incident
   - Events: incident_created, ai_summary_updated, status_changed, etc.

**Right Column**:
1. **Incident Metadata** card (id, traceId, tempId, team, assigned_to)
2. **Policy Violations** (`PolicyViolationList`):
   - List each policy that was triggered with violation text
3. **Related Alerts** card
4. **Actions**: Edit, Delete buttons

**Real-time**: Subscribe `incidents` room в†’ when `incident:analyzed` fires with this `incidentId`, auto-update `AIAnalysisCard` with animation (card fades in when data arrives)

**API calls**: `GET /incidents/:id`, `GET /audit-logs/entity/:id`, `GET /policy-logs?incident_id=:id`

---

### Page 5: Alerts (`/alerts`)
**Goal**: Alert management feed with acknowledge workflow.

**Components**:
- Filter bar: severity, acknowledged status
- `AlertFeed`: Cards sorted by newest first
  - Each card: incident source, severity badge, message, timestamp
  - **Acknowledge button** (green checkmark) в†’ optimistic update via TanStack Query
  - Unacknowledged в†’ glowing border
- Pagination

**Real-time**: `alert:created` event в†’ new card flies in at top with bounce animation + browser notification if permission granted

**API calls**: `GET /alerts`, `PATCH /alerts/:id/ack`

---

### Page 6: Knowledge Policies (`/policies`)
**Goal**: Manage AI firewall sanitization rules.

**Components**:
- Policy cards with:
  - Policy name + description
  - `blocked_keywords` chips (red tags)
  - `allowed_domains` chips (green tags)
  - Edit/Delete buttons
- **Create/Edit Policy Modal** (`PolicyForm`):
  - Name input
  - Blocked keywords вЂ” chip input (type + Enter to add)
  - Allowed domains вЂ” chip input
  - Zod validation

**Real-time**: Subscribe `policies` room в†’ `policy:violation` toast counter on this page

**API calls**: `GET /firewall/api/policies`, `POST /firewall/api/policies`, `PATCH /firewall/api/policies/:id`, `DELETE /firewall/api/policies/:id`

---

### Page 7: Audit Trail (`/audit`)
**Goal**: Compliance view вЂ” who did what, when.

**Components**:
- Filter bar: entity_type, action, date range
- **Audit log table**: 
  - columns: action, entity_type, entity_id (linked to incident), user, timestamp, details (expandable JSON)
- **Policy violations sub-tab**: shows `policy_logs` table

**API calls**: `GET /audit-logs`, `GET /policy-logs`

---

### Page 8: Settings (`/settings`)
**Goal**: User profile + team management + notification preferences.

**Tabs**:
1. **Profile** вЂ” Update name, email, password
2. **Team** вЂ” View team members, roles
3. **Notifications** вЂ” Toggle Slack/Email alerts (informational, actual config is backend env)
4. **API Keys** вЂ” Show project API key with copy button (for SDK integration)

---

## Real-Time Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as Frontend (Next.js)
    participant GW as Gateway (:3000)
    participant K as Kafka

    FE->>GW: socket.connect()
    FE->>GW: emit("subscribe:incidents")
    FE->>GW: emit("subscribe:alerts")

    K-->>GW: incident.created event
    GW-->>FE: emit("incident:created", payload)
    Note over FE: Toast + table row insert

    K-->>GW: incident.analyzed event
    GW-->>FE: emit("incident:analyzed", payload)
    Note over FE: AI card animates in on detail page

    K-->>GW: alert.created event
    GW-->>FE: emit("alert:created", payload)
    Note over FE: Alert badge pulses, card insert
```

### `useWebSocket` Hook Design
```typescript
const { isConnected, latestIncident, latestAlert } = useWebSocket({
  subscriptions: ["incidents", "alerts"], // rooms to join
  onIncidentCreated: (data) => { /* add to query cache */ },
  onIncidentAnalyzed: (data) => { /* update incident in cache */ },
  onAlertCreated: (data) => { /* increment badge, show toast */ },
  onPolicyViolation: (data) => { /* show violation toast */ },
})
```

---

## Data Flow Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Auth Flow"
        LOGIN["Login Form"] --> API_LOGIN["POST /users/login"]
        API_LOGIN --> ZUSTAND["Zustand authStore\n{ user, token }"]
        ZUSTAND --> AXIOS["Axios interceptor\nAttaches Bearer token"]
    end

    subgraph "Data Fetching"
        HOOKS["Custom hooks\n(useIncidents, useAlerts...)"] --> TANSTACK["TanStack Query\nCache + Refetch"]
        TANSTACK --> AXIOS
        AXIOS --> GATEWAY["API Gateway :3000"]
    end

    subgraph "Real-Time"
        SOCKET_HOOK["useWebSocket hook"] --> SOCKETIO["Socket.io client"]
        SOCKETIO --> GW_WS["Gateway WebSocket"]
        GW_WS --> CACHE_UPDATE["queryClient.setQueryData()"]
    end
```

---

## Proposed Pages API Map

| Page | GET calls | POST/PATCH/DELETE |
|---|---|---|
| `/login` | вЂ” | POST /users/login |
| `/register` | вЂ” | POST /users/register |
| `/` (dashboard) | GET /stats, GET /incidents?limit=10, GET /alerts?acknowledged=false | вЂ” |
| `/incidents` | GET /incidents (paginated) | POST /incidents, DELETE /incidents/:id |
| `/incidents/:id` | GET /incidents/:id, GET /audit-logs/entity/:id, GET /policy-logs?incident_id=:id | PATCH /incidents/:id |
| `/alerts` | GET /alerts (paginated) | PATCH /alerts/:id/ack |
| `/policies` | GET /firewall/api/policies | POST, PATCH, DELETE /firewall/api/policies |
| `/audit` | GET /audit-logs, GET /policy-logs | вЂ” |
| `/settings` | GET /users/:id | PATCH /users/:id |

