## Implementation Notes

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Authentication**: JWT is stored in Zustand + `localStorage`. The Axios interceptor reads the token and attaches `Authorization: Bearer <token>` to every request. On 401, auto-redirect to `/login`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **CORS**: The gateway already has CORS enabled (`app.use(cors())`). The frontend can call `http://localhost:3000` directly (or env var `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Policy routes**: Knowledge policies go through `/firewall/*` in the gateway via the `firewallRouter`. The frontend calls `GET /firewall/api/policies`, `POST /firewall/api/policies`, etc.

> [!TIP]
> **Real-time + TanStack Query**: When a WebSocket event fires, call `queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['incidents'] })` OR use `queryClient.setQueryData()` for instant optimistic updates without re-fetching.

> [!NOTE]
> **Stats endpoint is public** (no auth) вЂ” the gateway stats route does not require `authenticate`. This allows the dashboard to show a preview even before login (could be a landing/teaser).

> [!WARNING]
> **Firewall routes for policies**: The gateway's `firewall.routes.ts` proxies to `:4002`. Make sure to verify that policies CRUD is mounted and accessible through `GET /firewall/api/policies` before building the policies page.

